Now let me talk about each of these in more detail. 

## 1. Archaic/Instinctive - BEIGE

In this pattern, an individual apprehends their surroundings directly, and responds to stimuli with instinctive action, unmediated by communication with others, or cultural influences, and unburdened by any abstract knowledge.

## 2. Magical/Animistic - PURPLE

In this pattern humans organize themselves into tribes, and try to protect themselves from danger through use of magical symbols, and through appeals to mythical gods and creatures.

This may sound primitive, but every significant modern sports team has its own mascot, its team colors, its symbol/logo, and its traditional heroes. In my case, as a graduate of the University of Michigan, I have the [Block M](https://alumni.umich.edu/michigan-alum/history-lessons-the-block-m-in-brief/), the colors of maize and blue, and the legendary figure of Bo Schembechler. When I come across someone else sporting these colors and symbols, then I acknowledge our tribal bond and shared history by shouting out "Go Blue!" These are all examples of the Magical/Animistic pattern. 

